        <h1>LeetCode 1344: Angle Between Hands of a Clock (C++)</h1>
        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                Given two numbers, hour and minutes, return the smaller angle (in degrees) formed between the hour and
                the minute hand of a clock. Answers within 10^-5 of the actual value will be accepted.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: hour = 12, minutes = 30<br>
                Output: 165.0<br>
                Explanation: The minute hand is at 180° (30 × 6°). The hour hand is at 15° (12 × 30° + 30 × 0.5°). The
                gap is |15 - 180| = 165°. The smaller angle is min(165, 360-165) = 165°.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    double angleClock(int hour, int minutes) {
        double hrAngle = hour * 30.0 + minutes * 0.5;
        double minAngle = minutes * 6.0;
        double gap = abs(hrAngle - minAngle);
        // Clock hands form two angles; choose the smaller one
        return min(gap, 360.0 - gap);
    }
};</code></pre>
